news.title: Trident Realty acquires 200-acre land in Panchkula
news.para: Trident Realty paid Rs 160 crore to HDFC, Rs 65 crore to Axis Bank, and Rs 95 crore to the Haryana government as part of the resolution process. It has also taken a credit line of Rs 100 crore from IndusInd Bank.

news.title: Godrej Properties buys 50 acres land parcel in Palghar
news.para: The proposed project will offer a booking value potential of approximately Rs 500 crore. It is estimated to have a developable potential of approximately 1.2 million sq ft of saleable area comprising primarily of residential plotted development.

news.title: Guwahati: Ban on piling building materials on roadsides from 6am-10pm
news.para: On Wednesday, the GMC imposed a penalty of Rs 7,000 and Rs 4,000 on two construction material dealers located on Kanakalata road in the Hengrabari area of the city.

news.title: Rajasthan housing boards earned Rs 2,327.90 crore in 2021-22
news.para: From a little over Rs 100 crore in 2018-19, the housing board has earned a whopping Rs 2,327.90 crore in 2021-22 mostly by selling over 16,000 residential units and close to 3,000 shops across the state.

news.title: Odisha to prepare five-year perspective plan for development of peri-urban areas
news.para: The chief secretary discussed the need for seamless communication between fast moving urban centers with peri-urban areas. He said urban centers provide employment and livelihood opportunities to the people.

news.title: On tax hunt, Chandigarh civic body finds 300 properties without owners
news.para: The staff found these properties locked or sealed by other departments or not allotted. As a result, no name of property owner and address was found in the records.

news.title: Ludhiana: Applicants' wait gets longer as PMAY files under scrutiny
news.para: Since the scheme is still going on and there are many applications pending for payment, as of now the payments have been stopped and staff is sending the applicants back by asking them to wait for at least two months.

news.title: Sebi's refund to Sahara investors reach Rs 138 crore since 2012
news.para: The remaining applications were closed either due to their records not being traceable in the documents or data provided by two Sahara Group firms -- Sahara India Real Estate Corporation Ltd (SIREL) and Sahara Housing Investment Corporation Ltd (SHICL).

news.title: Telangana government to regularise land in 44 colonies in six assembly segments
news.para: As per GO 118 issued on October 28, a nominal amount of Rs 250 per square yard would be charged for regularisation. It has to be paid in four instalments within six months.

news.title: Maharashtra to push e-registration of first-sale units by developers
news.para: The total expected units to be registered from developers’ offices is around 1.43 lakh units in coming days, said officials. For now, daily registration is limited to 10-15 documents.

news.title: Flat owners in Maharashtra to get vertical property cards soon
news.para: “There have been discussions on the issue at the level of the revenue minister and the draft should be cleared soon. The rules would be issued thereafter,” a senior official of the revenue department said on Wednesday.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Sanghavi Realty buys 5,400 sq yard plot for Rs 160 crore
news.para: Ahmedabad-based developer Sanghavi Realty purchased the 5,400-square yard plot for an estimated Rs 160 crore for a commercial project, according to sources privy to the development.

news.title: SC reserves verdict on sale of unused FAR of Amrapali projects
news.para: The Noida and Greater Noida authorities have opposed the sale of the unused FAR while court receiver and attorney general R Venkataramani has supported it saying it will help in generating funds for the stalled projects of the group.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's profit falls 77% to Rs 47 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations increased 15.11 per cent to Rs 2,971 crore in the second quarter of the current fiscal. In the year-ago period, the same stood at Rs 2,581 crore.

news.title: China Evergrande unit gets notice for $4.48 billion loan from Shengjing Bank
news.para: The bank said it failed to recover funds totalling 32.595 billion yuan ($4.48 billion), which was provided to the unit from 2020 to 2021, according to Evergrande.
